luations. </p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">In his classic <em>A Random Walk Down Wall Street</e=
m>, Burton Malkiel wrote, &#8220;A blindfolded monkey throwing darts at a n=
ewspaper&#8217;s financial pages could select a portfolio that would do jus=
t as well as one carefully selected by experts.&#8221; Were the Princeton e=
conomist writing an updated version today, he might say, &#8220;A blindfold=
ed monkey throwing darts at Robinhood could select a tech stock that would =
have doubled over the past year.&#8221;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">And it&#8217;s not just=
 public tech stocks. Private market tech company valuations have soared too=
, with companies raising seed rounds at $20 million pre-revenue, Series A&#=
8217;s at valuations in the hundreds of millions, and Series B&#8217;s wort=
h a billion. <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxNkMuOhSAMQL_msh=
vDQ7y4YDGb-Q3Doyq5CgZwjH8_HU3uTFJKQ9OccpypMKV86i2VSn7TUM8NdISjLFArZLIXyEPwm=
